Lucille Ball, 77, died early Wednesday while recovering from heart surgery.
She was the  queen of television comedy.
She and her husband Desi Arnaz created "I Love Lucy"  with its weekly wackiness watched by 40 million.
Born in upstate New York, she was a  chorus girl and model before Hollywood.
"I Love Lucy" was the first TV comedy to be  filmed, leaving a legacy of reruns.
After her divorce from Arnaz, Miss Ball married Gary  Morton and starred in other shows.
"Here's Lucy" included her two children.
In later  life she appeared in several movies and garnered awards and tributes. 
